&lt;p&gt;We need someone who embodies three qualities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are a full-stack builder.&lt;/strong&gt; You think in complete systems. You can design the flow, reason through the architecture, and understand how data moves. You arrive with something real - rough wireframes, a concrete proposal with sharp scope and tradeoffs - so that Engineering and Design can react, improve, and ship. When you do this well, execution accelerates because translation is no longer required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are a creative.&lt;/strong&gt; You understand that great product doesn&#39;t emerge in a straight line. You&#39;re comfortable sitting in ambiguity long enough to find something genuinely good, but not so long that nothing ships. You know when to open up possibilities and when to collapse them into something real. You create space when it&#39;s needed and apply pressure when it&#39;s time to get a a project over the line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are a sleuth.&lt;/strong&gt; The organization will hand you noise - feature requests from brand partners, sales team asks, competitor moves, partial diagnoses. You assume what you&#39;re hearing is filtered, incomplete, or slightly wrong. You read between the lines, apply trained product judgment, and uncover the real problem worth solving. You don&#39;t take things at face value. You do the work to find the truth underneath.&lt;/p&gt;
